results.name: Difference between value of n, when remultiplied "upward", from GF(2)[X] to N, and when remultiplied "downward", from N to GF(2)[X]: a(n) = A234742(n) - A234741(n).
comment: a(n) = 0 iff both A236378(n) and A236379(n) are zero, or in other words, iff A234741(n)=n and A234742(n)=n, which means that A235032 gives all such n, that a(n) = 0.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8191
xref: A235032 gives the positions of zeros, A235033 the positions of nonzeros.
